About this item

  • Google Nest Thermostat E - Programmable Smart Thermostat for Home T4000ES - 3rd Generation Nest Thermostat (Frosted White)- Works with Alexa
  • Programmable smart thermostat that learns the temperatures you like and programs itself to help you save energy and stay comfortable. Nest Thermostat E is Easy to install. Most people can install it in under 60 minutes, and it works with most heating and cooling systems, and its frosted display is beautifully designed to blend right in.
  • The Nest Leaf appears when you choose a temperature that saves energy; with Energy History, just check your phone to see how much energy you used and find out how to save more. Home/Away Assist automatically adjusts itself to an Eco Temperature after you leave, so you dont heat or cool an empty home. Remote control lets family members change the temperature on this smart thermostat from anywhere using a phone, laptop, or tablet
  • Start with a simple schedule and easily adjust it whenever you like in the Nest app. Works with Alexa, Google Assistant, and other smart speakers so you can adjust the temperature with your voice.
  • Along with the Nest Thermostat E, this Value Bundle also includes 1 Nest Temperature Sensor to help make sure a certain room is the exact temperature you want it to be. Put temperature sensors in different rooms. And choose which room to prioritize when.
  • Save time with the Google Nest Compatibility Checker. Google Nest offers a helpful and informative online tool so that you determine if the Nest thermostat is compatible with your heating and cooling system.
  • Mounting type: Wall Mount

Product Description

The Nest Thermostat E is a smart thermostat that turns itself down when youre away. It helps you save energy and keep your home comfortable. You can control it from anywhere with the Nest app, and it works with Alexa and Google Assistant so you can adjust the temperature with your voice. Nest Thermostat E is compatible with 85% of systems, and its frosted display is beautifully designed to blend right in. Independent studies showed that Nest thermostats saved people an average of 10% to 12% on heating and 15% on cooling. Individual savings may differ.

Technical Specifications:

  • Size and weight: Mass: 4.9 oz (139 g) | Diameter: 3.19 in (8.1 cm) | Height: 1.14 in (2.89 cm)
  • Color: White
  • Screen: 24-bit color LCD | 320 x 320 resolution at 182 pixels per inch | 1.76 in (4.5 cm) diameter
  • Languages: English (US, UK) | Dutch | French (Canada, France) | Italian | Spanish (Americas, Spain)
  • Compatibility: The Nest Thermostat E works with 85% of 24V heating and cooling systems, including gas, electric, forced air, heat pump, radiant, oil, hot water, solar and geothermal. | Heating and Cooling: 1 stage of heating (W1) and cooling (Y1) and a second stage of either heating (W2) or cooling (Y2). | Heat pump: with auxiliary and emergency heat (O/B, AUX) Fan (G) | Power (C, Rh or Rc) | The Nest Thermostat E is designed to work even if your home doesn't have a common (C) wire, but installing a new C wire may be required.
  • Sensors: Temperature | Humidity | Proximity/Occupancy | Ambient light
  • Battery: Built-in rechargeable lithium-ion battery
  • Power consumption: Less than 1 kWh/month
  • Connectivity requirements: Wi-Fi internet connection | Phone or tablet running iOS or Android | Nest app
  • Wireless: 802.11b/g/n 2.4GHz, 802.11a/n 5GHz | 802.15.4 @ 2.4GHz | Bluetooth Low Energy
  • Certification: UL 60730-1, Standard for Safety Automatic Controls | UL 60730-2-9, Particular Requirements for Temperature Sensing Controls | ENERGY STAR
  • Green: RoHS compliant | REACH compliant | Recyclable packaging | Title 20 battery charger compliant

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
5 out of 5 stars
More comfortable home! Really good technology for saving on energy costs
This thermostat was super easy to install and set up. I wired it, popped it on the mount, entered my information, let it update, left it on automatic "learn" schedule and just let it rock. My house doesn't have any returns for the forced air system upstairs, so the upstairs gets very hot in the winter at night and the heat runs a lot. The remote temperature sensor (which comes with this kit) solved this problem very well. I have it set to work off the upstairs temperature sensor during the "night" schedule which by default is 10pm to 7am, which ended up being perfect for us. It makes the upstairs so much more comfortable at night and the heat runs a lot less. Just a quick catch-up when it switches back to the downstairs thermostat in the morning. Adding the remote temperature sensor in the settings is also a breeze, especially with the Nest app. And overall, it seems like this thermostat works more "smoothly" than the cheap battery-powered one we had before. The heat doesn't seem to run as long and create as many uncomfortably high temperature events as the old thermostat. The occupancy sensor and automatic "away" eco temperature settings also work very well. It almost immediately recognizes when nobody is home and switches the settings. We also have central air, so I may post an update on how well it works with that when summer comes.Note about installation: This thermostat is powered by the furnace, therefore requires the blue "common" wire to charge the thermostat battery. I thought I was missing the blue wire but it turned out the previous installer just cut it back at the cable sheath. I simply slid a little more slack through in the basement, re-stripped the cable, and got the blue wire back. Note I also precharged the thermostat with the USB micro port while I was working on fixing the wiring. Not sure if that was necessary, but it was completely off/dead when I received it.

  • kash
    5.0 out of 5 stars More comfortable home! Really good technology for saving on energy costs
    Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    This thermostat was super easy to install and set up. I wired it, popped it on the mount, entered my information, let it update, left it on automatic "learn" schedule and just let it rock. My house doesn't have any returns for the forced air system upstairs, so the upstairs gets very hot in the winter at night and the heat runs a lot. The remote temperature sensor (which comes with this kit) solved this problem very well. I have it set to work off the upstairs temperature sensor during the "night" schedule which by default is 10pm to 7am, which ended up being perfect for us. It makes the upstairs so much more comfortable at night and the heat runs a lot less. Just a quick catch-up when it switches back to the downstairs thermostat in the morning. Adding the remote temperature sensor in the settings is also a breeze, especially with the Nest app. And overall, it seems like this thermostat works more "smoothly" than the cheap battery-powered one we had before. The heat doesn't seem to run as long and create as many uncomfortably high temperature events as the old thermostat. The occupancy sensor and automatic "away" eco temperature settings also work very well. It almost immediately recognizes when nobody is home and switches the settings. We also have central air, so I may post an update on how well it works with that when summer comes.

    Note about installation: This thermostat is powered by the furnace, therefore requires the blue "common" wire to charge the thermostat battery. I thought I was missing the blue wire but it turned out the previous installer just cut it back at the cable sheath. I simply slid a little more slack through in the basement, re-stripped the cable, and got the blue wire back. Note I also precharged the thermostat with the USB micro port while I was working on fixing the wiring. Not sure if that was necessary, but it was completely off/dead when I received it.
